$interpreted: Naya: ...The census has been completed in the distant, domestic villages. But we discovered some areas still exist in scattered bandit settlements.
Naya: We'll need to periodically send in forces for protection.
Angelia: ...Oh...
Sione: We've already found an architect to estimate the new castle's expansion project. If it's convenient, could we find time to...
Angelia: ...Oh, okay...
Naya: Angel?
Angelia: Got it. We need to send someone to protect the bandits in the distant villages. I'll send the Royal Architect out on patrol.
Sione: ...Angel, did you just dozed off?
Sione: Angel, you've been working too hard. You ought to rest.
Angelia: Please, relax. I rest every day at noon...
Naya: That doesn't count! You should put everything down. I think you need to take a break and travel far away, or to another country.
Naya: Otherwise, if you keep it up like this, your body won't be able to take it any longer!
Sione: Naya's right. All government affairs are on track. If you want to go somewhere for vacation, everybody will be understanding.
Angelia: I know all you are worried about me, but now is different from before.
Angelia: Now that I'm Queen, everywhere I go everyone is paying attention to everything I do. Even if I leave the country it turns into State diplomacy.
Angelia: Even though it's a simple outing, General Levon will have to send troops for protection. Everyone's workload will increase.
Angelia: I'm not allowed to be selfish and think only of myself.
Naya: *sigh*...can't we just let Angel relax and have a nice vacation?
Sione: ...I know someone who can help us think of a way...
？？？: You want a lazy deserter? Take me!
Naya: You've really got a plan?
Fredrica: As a Queen, it doesn't matter where you go, you're going to be harassed. Why don't we go somewhere where nobody recognizes the Queen?
Fredrica: Maple Lake is not only remote and deserted, but it's also a beautiful environment. It's the Holy Land of vacations~
Sharice: Did the General bring me here so I could accompany the Queen on the road?
Sione: Sounds pretty good, but General Levon...
Fredrica: Let's first give him a mission that requires a few days before reporting back, then before he returns we'll hurry back. No problem~
Fredrica: Sharice is familiar with the road to Maple Lake, she can help save time.
Fredrica: To prevent any unforeseen circumstances, we'll need two bodyguards for the Queen and someone to stay behind to cover for those that have left.
Fredrica: This plan to skip work is flawless!
Sione: As expected from General Lucien. When it's about getting out of work, your brain works even faster than Hyde's.
Naya: Nonetheless, this way Angel will have a chance to have some fun!
Angelia: Is this...really a good idea?
Naya: It's just a few days. Nothing will happen.
Sione: If something is wrong, General Lucien will notify us. We'll definitely have the time to return.
Fredrica: Right. Our secret messenger will be...
Fredrica: Wait. This idea was all mine. Why do you all get to go play while I have to stay here?
Sione: General Lucien, your rank is the highest among us. If you stay and cover for us, won't this be the most convincing?
Angelia: Plus, you used all your vacation days as soon as the new year started. If you go play, I'm a bit worried about your progress at work...
Fredrica: Who cares about work when you can play! Whatever, if you won't let me go, I'm going to tell handsome you're all planning on leaving!
Naya: What? Grab her!
Fredrica: Bloody Mary! Let me go! If I can't go, don't you think about going!
Sharice: Your Majesty the Queen, let me handle this! I've seen Jerome handle the General's tricks a million times already.
Sharice: General, going there's no use anyway. Maple Lake is full of animals and Beasts.
Sharice: There's not even half of a human, so there's no way you'll find a good man there.
